pt.ist.fenixframework

Class DomainMetaClass

  • java.lang.Object
    • pt.ist.fenixframework.core.AbstractDomainObject
      • pt.ist.fenixframework.DomainMetaClass_Base
        • pt.ist.fenixframework.DomainMetaClass
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, DomainObject

    public class DomainMetaClass
extends DomainMetaClass_Base
    A DomainMetaClass is the domain entity that represents a class existing in the application's domain model, declared in the DML.
    These DomainMetaClasses are created or deleted only during the FenixFramework initialization. A DomainMetaClass is linked to one superclass and many subclasses, which are also DomainMetaClasses.
    Each DomainMetaClass stores a set of all existing DomainMetaObjects of it's class. Furthermore, a DomainMetaClass contains a set of all DomainConsistencyPredicates that are declared in its code.

    • Field Detail

      • COMPARATOR_BY_CLASS_HIERARCHY_TOP_DOWN

        public static Comparator<Class<? extends DomainObject>> COMPARATOR_BY_CLASS_HIERARCHY_TOP_DOWN
        Compares two classes according to their hierarchies, such that a superclass always appears before any of its subclasses. Classes of different hierarchies are sorted alphabetically according to the names of their successive superclasses (from top to bottom).

      • COMPARATOR_BY_META_CLASS_HIERARCHY_TOP_DOWN

        public static Comparator<DomainMetaClass> COMPARATOR_BY_META_CLASS_HIERARCHY_TOP_DOWN
        Compares two DomainMetaClasses according to their hierarchies, such that a superclass always appears before any of its subclasses. DomainMetaClasses of different hierarchies are sorted alphabetically according to the names of their successive superclasses (from top to bottom).

        COMPARATOR_BY_CLASS_HIERARCHY_TOP_DOWN

      • initExistingDomainObjects

        protected void initExistingDomainObjects()
        This method should be called only during the initialization of the FenixFramework, for each new DomainMetaClass. Creates a DomainMetaObject for each existing DomainObject of the specified class, and associates the new DomainMetaObject to its DomainMetaClass.

      • executeInheritedPredicates

        public void executeInheritedPredicates()
        This method should be called only during the initialization of the FenixFramework. Executes any inherited consistency predicates from the superclasses that are not being overridden, for each existing object of this DomainMetaClass.

      • getAllConsistencyPredicates

        public Set<DomainConsistencyPredicate> getAllConsistencyPredicates()
        Returns a Set with all the DomainConsistencyPredicates that affect the objects of this class.
        Returns:
        a Set of all the DomainConsistencyPredicates declared directly by this class, or inherited and not overridden.

      • delete

        protected void delete()
        This method should be called only during the initialization of the FenixFramework.
        Deletes this DomainMetaClass, and all its metaSubclasses. Also deletes all the declared DomainConsistencyPredicates.
        A DomainMetaClass should be deleted only when the corresponding domain class is removed from the DML, or the framework is configured not to create meta objects.
